descriptionMarkdown:
(EN)

The Hydra project is a revolution in platform construction. The basis is taken from the Fish platform. (https://www.factorio.school/view/-ONiTEawPd2L5uEAYz_O). The platform is self-sufficient. Nothing needs to be sent from the planets. The platform control mode is the same as the Fish platform. The standard is set to Average speed. Modules "L" and "R" - can be added in UNLIMITED quantities.There is only ONE limitation - Additional modules can only be installed on the right and left sides respectively, with a slight adjustment in height. This is a Beta version. IMPORTANT - when adding additional sections - make a docking of the cargo compartment. This modularity is good to use in a co-op. On Nauvis you can create several additional sections, and when you arrive on another planet - disassemble the additional sections. Then send the components from orbit to the planet. And on this planet you can start building a BASE for another new platform. The platform is built on Tier 1 components, if you want you can build on Tiers 2,3,4 or Legendary. Just set UPGRADE in the blueprint and choose any upgrade. Created by GSXR.
